Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of water to boil. Mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Finely chop @chili pepper{1}(finely chopped), removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Cut any big @broccoli florets{8%oz}(cut into small, bite-size pieces). Halve @lime{1}(halved).

Combine @ground pork{10%oz}, scallion whites, @Thai seasoning blend{1%tsp}, half the garlic, and @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{to taste} in a medium #bowl. Form into 1-inch meatballs (about the size of a gumball).

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-4%minutes}. Pour @water{1/4%cup} into #pan, cover, and let meatballs steam until nearly cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Uncover, reduce heat to low, and let water evaporate.

Remove meatballs from #pan and set aside on a #plate. Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in same #pan over medium-high heat. Add broccoli and cook, tossing, until tender and lightly crisped, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}. Remove from #pan and set aside.

> TIP: If you're having trouble getting the broccoli to cook, add 1 TBSP water to pan to steam it.

Add half the @yakisoba noodles{8%oz} from package to #pot of boiling water (use the rest as you like). Cook, stirring, until al dente, ~{2-3%minutes}. Drain, then rinse under cold water. Add remaining @garlic{1%clove}(minced), chili (to taste), and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} to pan used for broccoli over medium-high heat. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Add noodles and toss to loosen.

Stir together @soy sauce{3%tbsp}, @honey{1/2%tbsp}, @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, and @water{1/4%cup} in a small #bowl.

> We sent more soy sauce and honey.

Lower heat under #pan with noodles to medium and add another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}. Add meatballs, broccoli, and soy sauce mixture to #pan. Cook, tossing, until combined and sauce clings to noodles, ~{1-2%minutes}. Divide between #bowls{}, then top with scallion greens and squeeze over a bit of lime.